10:59 AM Defendant Myisha Renee Honeycutt not in court.  Attorney Pablo Galaviz in court for Myisha Renee Honeycutt.  Prosecuting attorney Jack A. Pitzo in court for the State of Wisconsin. 

Attorney Galaviz states the defendant had some confusion today and thought her hearing was at the Washington County Courthouse as she has a pending matter there.  
Attorney Galaviz requests a stayed capias and to set this matter to Friday for a waiver of preliminary hearing.
The State has no objection to staying a capias until Friday with the knowledge the State will not be producing a witness given the information this matter will be a waiver.
The Court puts on record that it was notified the defendant had been calling the Clerk's office in regards to the mix up on her location today and has been in contact with Attorney Galaviz.  
Court ordered a warrant stayed until next court date and sets for a waiver of preliminary hearing to Friday, October 7, 2022.
